# SWAY notes
2021-08-01


grim - screenshot taker for wayland; only command-line version??
slurp - select a region in wayland and print it to stdout. works well with grim

kanshi - dynamic display profiles; equivalent for autoandr

mako - lightweight wayland notification daemon

rofi - window switcher, application launcher, dmenu replacement

sway
swaybg
swayidle
swaylock

waybar

wlroots
xdg-desktop-portal-wlr
   wlroots backend
   
   in sway cfg:
     exec dbus-update-activation-environment --systemd WAYLAND_DISPLAY XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP=sway

   in gdm desktop
     sudo vim /usr/share/wayland-sessions/sway.desktop      
     X-GDM-SessionRegisters=true
    
   if not showing up -> NVIDIA prorietary driver does not support wayland


# 2025-02-17

Brave/Chrome does not open File Open / Save dialogs in sway (wayland)

https://discussion.fedoraproject.org/t/blink-based-browsers-dont-open-file-dialog-in-sway-fedora-38/90403/3

had the same issue, I fixed it by adding gnome;sway to UseIn in /usr/share/xdg-desktop-portal/portals/gtk.portal
without this config there is no dbus interface org.freedesktop.impl.portal.FileChooser
not sure what should be the default interface for sway or how it was working previously
log out log back in


Open Brave Browser with native Wayland drawing (nicer fonts!!)

cp /usr/share/applications/brave-browser.desktop ~/.local/share/applications/

vim ~/.local/share/applications/brave-browser.desktop


Exec=brave-browser --enable-features=UseOzonePlatform --ozone-platform=wayland %U



